  "texts": [
    "The standard Heisenberg Uncertainty Principle (HUP), represents a cornerstone of quantum mechanics.",
    "However, the incorporation of gravity into quantum frameworks has long suggested the necessity of modifying this relation.",
    "While high energy (ultraviolet) modifications have been extensively explored through the Generalized Uncertainty Principle (GUP), the large scale (infrared) regime remains comparatively underdeveloped.",
    "One natural extension in this direction is the Extended Uncertainty Principle (EUP), which introduces a long wavelength cutoff and has received increasing attention in the context of infrared modified gravity, black hole thermodynamics, and cosmology.",
    "In the EUP framework, a fundamental minimal measurable momentum arises as an infrared (IR) counterpart to the minimal length in GUP scenarios."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}